background-color: #ccc;"> a sketchy report</a>, which he has denied, that M=
usk talked to Putin before endorsing his annexation of parts of Ukraine.)=
=C2=A0He is a man with many weird hobbies, but this is a particularly odd h=
obby, and as far as I can tell a <em>new=C2=A0</em>one. One possibility her=
e is that (as he says) he is worried about the risk of nuclear war and want=
s to defuse geopolitical tensions by tweeting polls or whatever. Another po=
ssibility is that China is a critical market for Tesla Inc., and he is seek=
ing China=E2=80=99s favor.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the fancier=C2=A0possibility is that he is=
 trying to=C2=A0<em>get American government officials worried</em>, so that=
 they will step in to block the Twitter deal. =E2=80=9CWe can=E2=80=99t let=
 Twitter, the =E2=80=98town square=E2=80=99 of American political discourse=
, be owned by a guy who might be a Chinese or Russian agent, so we have to =
block the deal,=E2=80=9D people think Musk thinks the government=C2=A0will =
think. By winkingly hinting=C2=A0that he might be doing Vladimir Putin=E2=
=80=99s bidding, the theory goes, Musk will force the US government to <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29351707.292269/aHR0cH=
M6Ly9ob21lLnRyZWFzdXJ5Lmdvdi9wb2xpY3ktaXNzdWVzL2ludGVybmF0aW9uYWwvdGhlLWNvb=
W1pdHRlZS1vbi1mb3JlaWduLWludmVzdG1lbnQtaW4tdGhlLXVuaXRlZC1zdGF0ZXMtY2ZpdXM/=
